No one knows where neurons, the basic of human thought, come from. They are thought to have evolved once throughout the animal kingdom and perfected ever since. However, the newly revealed DNA sequencing of a comb jelly called &ldquo;Pacific sea gooseberry&rdquo;1 indicates this is not the case, as it has evolved its own neural system independently of any other sea jelly.
)
So what? The brain is one of the most complex components of any anatomical system, maybe the most complicated thing in the universe - consisting of neurons, cerebral tissue, neurotransmitters, etc.
